'''Android''' is an operating system developed by the [http://www.openhandsetalliance.com/oha_overview.html Open Handset Alliance], led by Google, and mainly used on smartphones, tablets and multimedia boxes. It mainly runs on the {{Keyword|ARM}} 6 and 7 architecture, but it has also been ported to {{Keyword|x86}} and {{Keyword|MIPS}}. It uses the Linux kernel with a custom userland which is Apache licensed.

Gentoo has some Android-specific packages:

* {{package|dev-util/android-studio}}
* {{package|dev-util/android-sdk-update-manager}}
* {{package|dev-util/android-ndk}}
* {{package|app-mobilephone/qtadb}}
* {{package|dev-util/android-tools}}

